article.headline: Morehead St. 65, Tennessee St. 50
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Kenneth Faried had 23 points and 21 rebounds to lead Morehead State to a 65-50 win over Tennessee State on Thursday night. Maze Stallworth added 19 points and Demonte Harper had 10 for the Eagles (15-6, 9-1 Ohio Valley Conference), who have won 11 in a row. Both teams shot below 40 percent from the field, but a wide rebounding margin (45-32) made the difference for the Tigers. They pulled down 18 offensive boards. Morehead State led 28-22 at halftime and pushed the lead to 40-24 before Tennessee State made a 14-2 run to trim the lead to 42-38 on a tip-in by Lonnie Funderburk with 10:48 remaining. The Tigers built the lead back to 54-46, then made an 11-0 run for its largest lead at 65-46 with 1:36 to play. Two free throws by Stallworth capped the run. Darius Cox had 10 points and 10 rebounds for the Tigers (4-18, 1-9) and Jacquan Nobles also had 10.
